	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />If you're willing to open your NES and cut pin 4 of the lockout chip, then you can be assured that most aftermarket Fami-&gt;NES converters will work fine on any NTSC NES. Famicom games that use raster effects or the DMC might glitch on a PAL NES.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
