	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The reset signals are routed through the CIC chip (obviously, given the blinking that happens when it doesn't authenticate successfully), so it might be easier to disable it (cut pin 4) than to desolder it completely and reroute the reset signals.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


